      "caption": "Borealis - open data, code, weights recipe for training Audio LLM \u2014 Part 1 of 3.\n\n\ud83d\udc49 Swipe to see the full breakdown \u2192\n\nThe mix is what the model sees at training time with noise augmentation enabled. vLLM ships a closed set of multimodal architectures out of the box ( Qwen2-Audio , LLaVA , Phi-4-MM , a couple more).\n\n\ud83d\udd39 Don't dilute target-language data \"for diversity.\" 02 Adding plain-text instructions At 25%, the model starts forgetting the audio task .\n\u26a1 Where the 2.1\u00d7 comes from.\n\ud83e\udde0 Under the hood - serving and integrating with transformers Serving multimodal models isn't a new topic.\n\ud83d\udcca When the user writes a prompt with one <|AUDIO <|start_of_audio <|AUDIO <|start_of_audio as \"embedding will be supplied.\n\ud83d\udd2c The plugin ( vllm_borealis ) sits next to the weights in the HF model repo.\n\nWould you use something like this in your daily work? Yes or no in the comments.\n\n\ud83d\udcbe Save this post \u2014 you'll want to come back to this one.\n\n\ud83d\udcf0 Read the full stories:\n\ud83d\udd17 https://huggingface.co/blog/AlexWortega/borealis\n\ud83d\udd17 https://openai.com/index/grupo-folha-grupo-uol-partnership/\n\ud83d\udd17 https://www.anthropic.com/news/chris-olah-pope-leo-encyclical\n\ud83d\udd17 https://vllm.ai/blog/2026-04-28-nemotron-omni\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22273\n\n#LargeLanguageModels #LLMNews #LanguageModels #AIRegulation #TechLaw #AITools #ProductivityAI #AIProductivity #OpenAI #ChatGPT #GPT4 #GPT5 #GoogleAI #Gemini #AINews #TechNews #AIUpdates #ArtificialIntelligence #Tech #AI\n\n\u2500\n\u26a0\ufe0f This is not legal advice. Consult a qualified professional for guidance.\n\u2139\ufe0f Content curated & summarised by Graitech from the sources listed above. All rights remain with the original publishers.\n\u2500\n",
