      "caption": "Borealis - open data, code, weights recipe for training Audio LLM \u2014 Part 2 of 3.\n\n\ud83d\udc49 Swipe to see the full breakdown \u2192\n\nWe introduced the concept of ethics testing, discussed the challenges therewithin, and conducted five case studies to show how ethics testing can be performed for generative AI systems. Computer Science > Software Engineering Title: Ethics Testing: Proactive Identification of Generative AI System Harms Current browse context: References & Citations BibTeX formatted citation Bibliographic and Citation Tools Code.\n\n\ud83d\udd39 Generative Artificial Intelligence (GAI) systems that can automatically generate content in the form of source code or other contents.\n\u26a1 Misuse of the automatically generated content can incur serious consequences due to potential harms in the generated content.\n\ud83e\udde0 Despite the importance of ensuring the quality of automatically generated content, there is little to no approach that can systematically.\n\ud83d\udcca In this article, we introduce the novel concept of ethics testing which aims to systematically generate tests for identifying software harms.\n\ud83d\udd2c Computer Science > Software Engineering Title: Ethics Testing: Proactive Identification of Generative AI System Harms Current browse.\n\nDo you think OpenAI's move here is exciting or a risk? Drop your take below.\n\n\ud83d\udcbe Save this post \u2014 you'll want to come back to this one.\n\n\ud83d\udcf0 Read the full stories:\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22089\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22227\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22292\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22722\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.03963\n\n#LargeLanguageModels #LLMNews #LanguageModels #GenerativeAI #GenAI #AIRegulation #TechLaw #AIEthics #ResponsibleAI #OpenAI #ChatGPT #GPT4 #GPT5 #GoogleAI #Gemini #AINews #TechNews #AIUpdates #ArtificialIntelligence #FutureTech\n\n\u2500\n\u26a0\uf