      "caption": "Borealis - open data, code, weights recipe for training Audio LLM \u2014 Part 3 of 3.\n\n\ud83d\udc49 Swipe to see the full breakdown \u2192\n\narXiv is committed to these values and only works with partners that adhere to them. Computer Science > Cryptography and Security Title: Detecting Concept Drift in Evolving Malware Families Using Rule-Based Classifier Representations Current browse context: References & Citations BibTeX formatted citation Bibliographic and Citation Tools Code, Data and Media Associated with this Article Recommenders and Search Tools.\n\n\ud83d\udd39 Both individuals and organizations that work with arXivLabs have embraced and accepted our values of openness, community, excellence, and.\n\u26a1 Computer Science > Cryptography and Security Title: Detecting Concept Drift in Evolving Malware Families Using Rule-Based Classifier.\n\ud83e\udde0 The approach is evaluated across six malware families using fixed-interval and clustering-based windowing in family-vs-benign and.\n\ud83d\udcca These metrics are correlated with both accuracy degradation and data distribution shift as complementary drift indicators.\n\ud83d\udd2c Classifiers are trained across temporal windows on the EMBER2024 dataset, and drift is quantified by comparing extracted rule.\n\nWhich industry do you think will feel the impact of this first?\n\n\ud83d\udcbe Save this post \u2014 you'll want to come back to this one.\n\n\ud83d\udcf0 Read the full stories:\n\ud83d\udd17 https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22629\n\ud83d\udd17 https://english.khabarhub.com/2026/25/545711/\n\ud83d\udd17 https://thenextweb.com/news/meta-microsoft-layoffs-23000-ai-spending\n\ud83d\udd17 https://openai.com/index/grupo-folha-grupo-uol-partnership\n\ud83d\udd17 https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/info-tech/meta-microsoft-have-joined-tech-layoff-tsunami-but-is-ai-really-to-blame/article70907843.ece\n\n#LargeLanguageModels #LLMNews #LanguageModels #AIRegulation #TechLaw #AITools #ProductivityAI #